    schema:courseSchedule <https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/145016002/2025-26/eventSchedule> ;
    schema:description """The ultimate goal of the course is for the student to acquire the set of English language skills and abilities necessary for their communicative competence to align with the descriptors established for Level 4 (Operational) of the ICAO Rating Scale. The course is aimed at preparing students to pass the English language proficiency test, as established in Order FOM/896/2010 of April 6, published in the Official State Gazette (BOE) on April 13, 2010.
The course is part of a module that includes the subject Aeronautical English II, which is taught in the second semester of the third year of this degree programme.
The methods used (Check Your Aviation English by Emery & Roberts and Flightpath by Philip Shawcross) focus on mastering the linguistic elements and skills required for effective communication in non-routine situations. The study of standardized phraseology is reserved for other instructional contexts within the degree program. However, this course aims to provide an initial introduction to such phraseology using appropriate study materials. These contents will be supplemented with materials suited to practicing the vocabulary and communicative functions characteristic of aeronautical English."""@es ;
    schema:director <https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/m.camacho.diaz%40upm.es> ;
    schema:inLanguage "Inglés/Castellano"@es ;
    schema:instructor <https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/dulcinea.tomas%40upm.es>,
        <https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/m.camacho.diaz%40upm.es> ;
    schema:name "Inglés Aeronáutico II"@es .

