<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/145016002/2025-26/evaluation> a ns1:EvaluationSystem ;
    ns1:evaluationDescription """7.2. Assessment Criteria
Students enrolled in the course through continuous assessment will take two 'Progress tests'. The final grade will be the average of the grades obtained in each test, taking into account the established percentage for each, provided all tests are passed. If a student has not taken or passed one of them, they will have the opportunity to take the exam in the June session.
The dates for the intermediate assessment tests (2 Progress tests) may vary slightly based on the academic calendar. If, due to time constraints, it becomes necessary to adjust the schedule, this will be discussed in class.
Students who have chosen Aviation English + Flightpath will be assessed through the partial exams. Students who have chosen Aviation English + Business English will be assessed through partial exams for the Aviation English part and by developing and presenting a Business Plan. Students will be provided with guidelines on how to prepare and present their Business Plan.. The presentations must be uploaded to Moodle on the agreed date and presented on the agreed date between the students and the professor.
To pass the course, both the partial exams and the presentation of the Business Plan must have a grade of 5 out of 10. If any student fails one part, they will need to attend the ordinary exam session in June. If a student wishes to improve their grade, they will have the opportunity to do so in the June session by retaking all the partial exams. The final grade will be the one obtained in this exam.
The professor may increase the grade of students who have attended at least 80% of the classes and have actively participated, completing all activities and pending tasks.


7.2.1 Convocatoria extraordinaria de julio
Students who have failed one or both partial exams in either Aviation English or Flightpath must attend the July exam session. Students who have chosen Business English as their elective and have not submitted their Business Plan will need to do so in the extraordinary July session, where they will be required to present it.
The evaluation criteria focus on reading and writing comprehension of technical aerospace texts for Aviation English and Flightpath, and on presenting data in the format of presentations of texts and videos related to aviation business and management."""@es ;
    ns1:hasEvaluationTrial <https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/145016002/2025-26/evaluation/trial1>,
